Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Peel and slice the @sweet potato{1} and @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds.

Once boiling, add both types of potato to the water and simmer until just tender, ~{8-12%minutes}.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @medium tomato{2}.

== Breadcrumb Topping ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the @oil{1%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

== Creamy Pesto Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add half the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Stir the @fresh pesto{50%g} through the sauce, then taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== Assembly ==

Once ready, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and place them in layers in an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Pour over the creamy pesto sauce.

Sprinkle the crumbs evenly over the creamy potatoes.

Lay the tomato halves onto one side of a large #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread the tomatoes with the remaining garlic, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the gratin on the other side of the baking tray.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the gratin is golden brown and bubbling and the tomatoes have softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, share the gratin between your plates.

Serve the roasted tomatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%g} alongside, drizzling the @balsamic glaze{12%g} over the salad leaves to finish. Enjoy!